Appreciation post to my voice teacher @norapalka.sings 🌷🌷🌷

I’ve been working with Nora and @mattfarnsworthvoice since April and I’ve seen incredible strides in eight months. I never thought I’d be able to sing like this. I feel like they helped me find my voice again, find more joy, find more courage. Thank you both❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

Delicate Creatures is now available on Bandcamp ❤️‍🔥. Go to the link in my bio and click on “support for delicate creatures” to check it out. You can also send it as a gift to someone. Cute!!!

Today is my birthday 🥳. And since I’ve been radio silent on this platform for the last year I thought I’d share a bit about what this year looked like for me. Well, it really starts three years ago. My biggest dream was to be an opera singer and though it felt too late, I sought out classical voice teachers so I could, at the very least, work on beautiful Italian arias and challenge myself vocally. That’s when my TMJ disorder started. 

I’ve had excruciating jaw pain for three years now (though to be clear, there are moments, sometimes months, when it subsides, and I really savor those moments!). Of course, this is problematic as a singer. 

 I will never ever stop singing, but I have been challenged to find a balance so that it’s not ALL I’m doing. I’ve been trying to find a new path and sometimes the way looks wrong or unclear, but other times, the change is exciting. I have wracked my brain for a few years trying to answer the question, what will I do if I can’t sing anymore? And while I don’t have an answer I at least have some ideas that I’m working toward. 

I owe gratitude to my yoga studio @ariseinbrooklyn (@cloud_show_yoga ). Yoga has transformed my body and given me strength physically but also mentally. I used to think of myself as a chronically weak human but now I realize my body is capable of much more than I thought. 

This post isn’t meant to be a pity party but just a way to share this news as I feel a bit guilty that I haven’t been active with music in the way I once was. But I promise that deep inside of me, the creative wheels are still turning. And the art will be better than ever because I’ve taken the time to heal myself, inside and out. I have a clearer sense of who I am now. I’m trying to trust in the journey. I’m grateful for the challenge of growth, physically and mentally, the fact that I have been forced to expand myself in new ways. I’m stronger than I have ever been and it feels great. 

If you made it this far, happy holidays to you bb 💐🌟
